<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID="BEA6E9E7-96FB-5CD3-A300-BA08ADFF6729" authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Miogeometrida Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="73">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida chunjenshihi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chunjenshihi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida chunjenshihi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
The generic name is a combination of the prefix 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Mio-”">&quot;Mio-&quot;</normalizedToken>
in reference to the Miocene, and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“geometrid”">&quot;geometrid&quot;</normalizedToken>
in reference to the family name. The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis of genus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Body length ca 5.7 mm, wingspan ca 20 mm. Antenna filiform. Forewing without fovea, R1 not anastomosing with Sc, no areole formed by veins R1 and Rs, R1 and Rs1 completely coincident, M2 arising midway between M1 and M3, anal veins 1A and 2A fused for its entire length. Hind wing with Rs running close to Sc + R1, and M2 absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
The new genus can be distinguished from most extant or extinct geometrids by the absence of an areole formed by veins R1 and Rs. As 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. lacks M2 on the hind wing, affiliation with other subfamilies than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
is excluded. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. differs from most genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
in its forewing without fovea and R1 not anastomosing with Sc. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. is similar to genera such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wehrli" authorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Ekboarmia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ekboarmia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Ekboarmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="tribe" tribe="Boarmiini">Boarmiini</taxonomicName>
, covered in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/nl.40.10440" author="Skou, P" journalOrPublisher="Nota Lepidopterologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="39 - 63" refId="B44" refString="Skou, P, Stuening, D, Sihvonen, P, 2017. Revision of the West-Mediterranean geometrid genus Ekboarmia, with description of a new species from Portugal (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Ennominae). Nota Lepidopterologica 40 (1): 39 - 63, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/nl.40.10440" title="Revision of the West-Mediterranean geometrid genus Ekboarmia, with description of a new species from Portugal (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Ennominae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/nl.40.10440" volume="40" year="2017">Skou et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Iridopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iridopsis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Iridopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="tribe" tribe="Boarmiini">Boarmiini</taxonomicName>
, covered in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/entm109101fv" author="McGuffin, WC" journalOrPublisher="Washington Geology" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B30" refString="McGuffin, WC, 1977. Guide to the Geometridae of Canada (Lepidoptera) II. Subfamily Ennominae. 2. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 109(S101): 1-191. https://doi.org/10.4039/entm109101fv" title="Guide to the Geometridae of Canada (Lepidoptera) II. Subfamily Ennominae. 2. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 109 (S 101): 1 - 191." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/entm109101fv" year="1977">McGuffin 1977</bibRefCitation>
) in venation and the absence of a fovea, but the antennae of the latter are pectinated in males. Apart from this, extant 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Iridopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iridopsis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Iridopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much larger than 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. on average. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. also shows similarities with genera such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Milocera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Milocera" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Milocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kruger, 2001" authorityName="Kruger" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chelotephrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chelotephrina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Chelotephrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Tephrina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tephrina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Tephrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Isturgia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isturgia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Isturgia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Curtis, 1826" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Macaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Macaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1858" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="tribe" tribe="Macariini">Macariini</taxonomicName>
, covered in 
<bibRefCitation author="Krueger, M" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Natural History Museum Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 502" refId="B27" refString="Krueger, M, 2001. A revision of the tribe Macariini (Lepidoptera: Geometridae: Ennominae) of Africa, Madagascar and Arabia. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum Entomology 70 (1): 1 - 502" title="A revision of the tribe Macariini (Lepidoptera: Geometridae: Ennominae) of Africa, Madagascar and Arabia." volume="70" year="2001">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Krüger">Krueger</normalizedToken>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
) in the forewing with R1 and Rs1 completely coincident and hind wing with two anal veins, but 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. differs from them in its forewing with 1A and 2A fused for their entire lengths.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, DA" journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B8" refString="Grimaldi, DA, Engel, MS, 2005. Evolution of the Insects. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Evolution of the Insects." year="2005">Grimaldi and Engel (2005)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned three specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Leach" baseAuthorityYear="1815" family="Geometridae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="family">Geometridae</taxonomicName>
from Dominican amber and provided a photo and a line drawing of one specimen (
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, DA" journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B8" refString="Grimaldi, DA, Engel, MS, 2005. Evolution of the Insects. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Evolution of the Insects." year="2005">Grimaldi and Engel 2005</bibRefCitation>
: 588, fig. 13: 59, 60). According to the line drawing (
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, DA" journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B8" refString="Grimaldi, DA, Engel, MS, 2005. Evolution of the Insects. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Evolution of the Insects." year="2005">Grimaldi and Engel 2005</bibRefCitation>
: 588, fig. 13: 60), the stem of M is present on its forewing. But in 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov., the loss of the stem of M results in the formation of one large discal cell. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. differs from the Eocene species 
<taxonomicName authority="Kernbach, 1967" authorityName="Jarzembowski" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Geometridites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Geometridites larentiiformis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larentiiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Geometridites larentiiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of the areole and R1 completely coincident with Rs1 on the forewing. 
<bibRefCitation author="Merit, X" journalOrPublisher="Revue des Lepidopteristes de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="29 - 33" refId="B31" refString="Merit, X, Merit, M, 2008. Problongos baudiliensis genus novus &amp; species nova: un nouveau Lepidoptere fossile decouvert dans la diatomite du miocene superieur de Saint-Bauzile (Ardeche, F-07) (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Ennominae). Revue des Lepidopteristes de France 17 (39): 29 - 33" title="Problongos baudiliensis genus novus &amp; species nova: un nouveau Lepidoptere fossile decouvert dans la diatomite du miocene superieur de Saint-Bauzile (Ardeche, F- 07) (Lepidoptera, Geometridae, Ennominae)." volume="17" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mérit">Merit</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mérit">Merit</normalizedToken>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
reported Miocene 
<taxonomicName authority="Mérit &amp; Mérit, 2008" authorityName="Merit &amp; Merit" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Problongos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Problongos" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Problongos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose forewing length is twice as long as that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih, 2020" authorityName="Zhang, Shih &amp; Shih" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Miogeometrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Miogeometrida" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Miogeometrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. (22 mm vs. 8.9 mm).
</paragraph>
